  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My driving license is lost. How do I apply for a new one?",
  "response": "If you've lost your driving license, you\u2019ll need to apply for a replacement. The process can vary depending on your country or state, but here\u2019s a general guide on how to apply for a new license:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Apply for a Replacement Driving License:**\n\n1. **Report the Loss** (if required):  \n   - In some places, you may need to report the lost license to the local authorities or traffic department. Check if this is a requirement in your area.\n\n2. **Check Local Requirements**:  \n   - Visit the official website of your local Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV), Road Transport Authority (RTA), or equivalent agency to confirm the specific process and documents needed.\n\n3. **Gather Required Documents**:  \n   - Proof of identity (e.g., passport, national ID card, or birth certificate).  \n   - Proof of address (e.g., utility bill, rental agreement).  \n   - Police report (if required).  \n   - Application form (available online or at the office).  \n   - Passport-sized photos (if needed).  \n   - Fee payment (check the amount and payment method).\n\n4. **Visit the Local Office or Apply Online**:  \n   - Many agencies allow you to apply for a replacement license online. Check if this option is available in your area.  \n   - If you need to visit in person, schedule an appointment if possible to save time.\n\n5. **Pay the Fee**:  \n   - There is usually a fee for replacing a lost license. Payment can often be made online, at the office, or via other approved methods.\n\n6. **Receive Your Replacement License**:  \n   - Once your application is processed, you\u2019ll receive your new license. This may be mailed to you or issued on the spot, depending on your location.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**:  \n- If you\u2019re traveling or temporarily in another country, contact your home country\u2019s licensing authority for guidance.  \n- Keep a digital or physical copy of your license as a backup in case it\u2019s lost or stolen again.  \n\nFor specific details, visit the official website of your local licensing authority or contact their customer service.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
